<form class="form-horizontal">
	<div class="form-group" id="publications">
		<div class="col-md-12">
			<h4>Filters</h4>
			<p>You may use the following fields to filter the displayed
				graph:</p>
			<dl>
				<dt>Year</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>Displays collaborations performed in publications in the
						selected years. You might select a maximum of five "years" or let
						it empty to search for collaborations from all years.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Type</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>
						Collaborations performed in publications of the selected type.
						DBLP classifies publications using the following types: Journal
						Article, Conference and Workshop Papers, Parts in Books or
						Collections, Editorship, Reference Works and Informal and Other
						Publications. You can find more information about publications
						classification <a target="_blank"
							href="http://dblp.uni-trier.de/faq/What+types+does+dblp+use+for+publication+entries.html">here</a>.
					</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Venue</dt>
				<dd>Collaborations performed in publications from the selected
					years, e.g., CSCW - Conference on Computer Supported Cooperative
					Work, IEEE, CCIS - Communications in Computer and Information
					Science, books & theses, reference works, edited collections, and
					so on.</dd>
				<dt>Minimun number of collaborations</dt>
				<dd>Displays only collaborations that occurred at least 'n'
					times between the author and her coauthors, where 'n' is the number
					selected. For example, if I select the number '3', the graph will
					only displays edges with value 3 or higher.</dd>
			</dl>
			<p>
				<i>Obs: Those filters only dispose information that exists into
					the displayed graph. </i>
			</p>
			<br>
			<h4>Graph</h4>
			<p>You are free to manipulate the graph with some different
				interactions:</p>
			<dl>
				<dt>Mouse wheel</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>Zoom in/out.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Single click node</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>Highlight the node and its respective edges.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Double click edge</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>Displays a pop-up window with all resulting publications
						from collaborations between the author and the respective
						coauthor. Those publications will be displayed following a
						determined pattern of display, which is: [Title] [Type] ([Year])
						[link to the publication, if it exists].</p>

				</dd>
				<dt>Double click coauthor node</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>You'll be redirected to the graph page of the respective
						coauthor.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Click and drag node</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>You can click and drag the node to move it to other points
						in the screen.</p>
				</dd>
				<dt>Click and drag screen</dt>
				<dd>
					<p>You can click and drag the screen background to move it
						without changing the nodes position.</p>
				</dd>
			</dl>
		</div>
	</div>
</form>